Marjan Hussein has been appointed as the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) Chief Executive Officer (CEO) after emerging as the top candidate following recent interviews. Hussein has been holding the position in an acting capacity since 2018, when former CEO, Ezra Chiloba was fired. The Commission's Chairperson Wafula Chebukati while announcing the confirmation said Hussein was found to be the most suitable candidate from 5 shortlisted applicants. Interviews for Deputy CEO are ongoing for the 10 shortlisted applicants and are expected to end on March 10, 2022 according to Chebukati, reports Simon Ndonga for Capital FM. General elections are scheduled to be held on August 9, 2022. Voters will elect the president, members of the national assembly and senate, county governors and members of the 47 county assemblies.